The paper deals with facial landmark detection, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The authors propose a semi-supervised method that involves training an adversarial autoencoder, which is a type of deep learning model (cs.LG). The method also involves generating implicit knowledge about face appearance and shape, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions benchmarks such as AFLW and WLFW, which are datasets commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the speed of the framework, which could be related to neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
